---
title: Pea and Pancetta Penne with Parmesan, Pine Nuts, and Mint
description: Just a small amount of pancetta imparts bold flavor into any recipe. We love the combination of salty pancetta, sweet peas, and sharp parmesan cheese. This creamy pasta is guaranteed to please even the pickiest of eaters.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/56d5c3d94dab71ce7e8b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/56d5c3d94dab71ce7e8b4567.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/uk-super-quick-creamy-pasta-with-peas-and-pancetta-56d5c3d94dab71ce7e8b4567
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: Fusion
nutrition:
  calories: 637 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 9 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 27 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 645 mg
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Mince or grate the @garlic{4%clove}. Roughly chop the @mint{1/4%ounce} leaves.

Heat a large pan over medium-low heat. Add the @pine nuts{2%ounce} and toss for ~{2-3%minutes}, until lightly golden brown. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in the same pan over medium heat. Add the @pancetta{4%ounce} and cook, tossing for ~{2-3%minutes}, until slightly crispy. Stir in the garlic and @peas{8%ounce} and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}, until fragrant and heated through.

Boil the pasta: Add the @penne pasta{12%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for ~{9-11%minutes}, until al dente. Drain, reserving 1/3 cup pasta water.

Stir the @sour cream{8%tablespoon} into the pancetta mixture. Add the drained pasta and half the @parmesan cheese{1/2%cup} to the pan along with the @veggie stock concentrate{2%unit} and the reserved pasta water. Toss over medium heat until a creamy sauce forms, for ~{3-4%minutes}. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Plate and serve: Serve the pea and pancetta penne divided between bowls and sprinkled with the mint, pine nuts, and remaining parmesan cheese. Enjoy!